Due to the non-existence of experimental data for 51Cr, above     2428 1451
the inelastic threshold we adopted calculations from the nuclear  2428 1451
reaction model code EMPIRE-3.2.3 Malta (SVN rev.  5170; source    2428 1451
rev.  5168), using a parametrization based on the the one used    2428 1451
for 53Cr for this same set of chromium evaluations. That means    2428 1451
we also performed coupled-channel calculations using an           2428 1451
interpolated version of the dispersive soft-rotor optical         2428 1451
potential of Li et al. (RIPL #616), but assuming a rigid rotor,   2428 1451
labeled as RIPL #617. Fast capture was normalized to match        2428 1451
ENDF/B-VIII.0 at the inelastic threshold and preequilibirum was   2428 1451
adjusted to be around 1b at 14.1 MeV.                             2428 1451
